HEADWORD: Tamarin
<hw>Tam"a*rin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From the native
name in Cayenne.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of several
species of small squirrel-like South American monkeys of the genus
<gen>Midas</gen>, especially <spn>Midas ursulus</spn>.</def>⟦br⟧
